WEBVTT

00:00.209 --> 00:01.877
<i>Previously on "The Rookie"...</i>

00:01.877 --> 00:03.670
How serious are you about
becoming a training officer?

00:04.922 --> 00:07.466
Sir, I don't <i>want</i> to be a T. O.
I'm <i>going</i> to be a T. O.

00:07.466 --> 00:10.844
This is Sabrina Fowler,
the very talented new actress

00:10.844 --> 00:12.137
on "Hot Suspect."

00:12.137 --> 00:14.097
It's a pleasure.
[ Chuckles ]

00:14.097 --> 00:15.766
You know, my character,

00:15.766 --> 00:18.018
is having an affair
with a police sergeant.

00:18.018 --> 00:19.770
And his wife
likes to watch.

00:19.770 --> 00:21.313
Lieutenant Landon Briggs.

00:21.313 --> 00:23.315
I'm the Union --
President. Yes, I know.

00:23.315 --> 00:24.608
Nolan. You know what
the best part about

00:24.608 --> 00:25.901
being union president is?

00:25.901 --> 00:26.902
Power.

00:26.902 --> 00:28.862
The power to help the people
I like

00:28.862 --> 00:30.822
and hurt the people
I don't.

00:31.865 --> 00:35.369
[ Siren wailing ]

00:35.369 --> 00:37.538
[ Tires screech ]

00:37.538 --> 00:41.833
♪♪

00:41.833 --> 00:50.801
♪♪

00:50.801 --> 00:52.970
♪♪

00:52.970 --> 00:56.890
Hey. What, uh --
What seems to be the problem?

00:56.890 --> 00:59.768
Nothing.
Everyone's overreacting.

00:59.768 --> 01:01.645
Overreacting to what?

01:01.645 --> 01:04.022
[ Hissing ]

01:05.857 --> 01:08.694
♪ Oh, oh, oh, oh, oh,
oh, oh, oh, oh ♪

01:08.694 --> 01:09.861
Not it.

01:09.861 --> 01:11.905
♪ I'm gonna win for you ♪

01:11.905 --> 01:15.409
♪ Like I know you want me
to do ♪

01:15.409 --> 01:18.036
[ Jack crying ]

01:18.036 --> 01:19.454
[ <i>Cartoon music playing</i>
<i>on television</i> ]

01:19.454 --> 01:20.789
[ Groans ]

01:20.789 --> 01:22.958
<i>♪ Get up early</i>
<i>in the morning ♪</i>

01:22.958 --> 01:24.626
[ Clatter ]

01:24.626 --> 01:30.340
♪♪

01:30.340 --> 01:32.551
I'm sorry.
Um, I'm sorry.

01:32.551 --> 01:35.137
I-I meant to get up early and --
and make you breakfast.

01:35.137 --> 01:36.930
And I had this
whole Mother's Day thing

01:36.930 --> 01:37.931
planned with Jack --

01:37.931 --> 01:39.891
Jack's been
up for three hours.

01:39.891 --> 01:41.685
I have been
up for three hours.

01:42.686 --> 01:43.854
Is that cereal
in your hair?

01:43.854 --> 01:45.022
And applesauce.

01:45.022 --> 01:47.524
And, somehow,
banana under my boob.

01:47.524 --> 01:48.525
Mm.

01:48.525 --> 01:51.445
Okay, so...
how can I fix this?

01:51.445 --> 01:53.739
I need a shower.
Mm-hmm.

01:53.739 --> 01:54.865
And a nap.

01:54.865 --> 01:56.116
Uh...

01:56.116 --> 01:58.035
But we have Mother's Day brunch
with your mom later.

01:58.035 --> 01:59.286
Right. [ Sighs ]

01:59.286 --> 02:00.579
Mm.
New plan.

02:00.579 --> 02:03.248
Mm-hmm?
Shower, blow-out,

02:03.248 --> 02:06.293
mani-pedi, and some mimosas
with Patrice.

02:06.293 --> 02:09.338
Okay, so you're gonna take Jack
to the nail salon.

02:10.380 --> 02:12.924
No.
<i>You're</i> taking Jack.

02:12.924 --> 02:14.718
Right. I just -- I have
that thing with a client

02:14.718 --> 02:16.094
for the restaurant,
remember?

02:16.094 --> 02:19.723
Which [chuckles]
I'm gonna take Jack to.

02:21.475 --> 02:22.559
I love you.

02:22.559 --> 02:23.560
Happy Mother's Day.

02:23.560 --> 02:25.228
Mm-hmm.

02:25.228 --> 02:28.231
[ Jack crying ]

02:28.231 --> 02:31.318
Nolan. Hold up.

02:31.318 --> 02:33.779
I got some bad news.

02:33.779 --> 02:36.114
I'm hearing rumors that
the Union President

02:36.114 --> 02:38.325
is gonna make a move
against you.

02:38.325 --> 02:39.910
Not a surprise,
given how I showed him up

02:39.910 --> 02:40.952
at the City Council.

02:40.952 --> 02:42.245
Any idea what
he's planning?

02:42.245 --> 02:43.955
Not yet,
but I expect the worst.

02:43.955 --> 02:46.625
There's no hard rule on
the union delegate count.

02:46.625 --> 02:48.085
He can shrink
the number by one.

02:48.085 --> 02:50.253
And because I was the last one
in, I'd be the first one out.

02:50.253 --> 02:51.338
What do I do?

02:51.338 --> 02:53.298
You focus on your
T. O. exam next week.

02:53.298 --> 02:55.425
Don't let politics
derail your career.

02:55.425 --> 02:57.469
Oh, no, I've been studying
my ass off. I think I'm ready.

02:57.469 --> 02:58.470
Don't think it.

02:58.470 --> 02:59.721
Be it.

02:59.721 --> 03:01.640
Clearly, you don't have
time to waste.

03:01.640 --> 03:02.766
Are you calling me old?

03:02.766 --> 03:03.600
It was implied.

03:03.600 --> 03:05.060
[ Both laugh ]

03:05.060 --> 03:07.854
Hey, you know, why don't
I ride with you today?

03:07.854 --> 03:10.190
I can teach you some things that
are not in the study guide.

03:10.190 --> 03:12.067
One-on-one time with
a supervisor will strengthen

03:12.067 --> 03:13.193
your case
for a promotion.

03:13.193 --> 03:14.736
Sir, you don't have
to do that for me.

03:14.736 --> 03:16.154
Nolan, do you
want to be a T. O.?

03:16.154 --> 03:18.532
Absolutely.
Then don't do that
small-town

03:18.532 --> 03:20.325
"I hate to be a bother"
thing.

03:20.325 --> 03:22.285
You're being offered
an opportunity.

03:22.285 --> 03:23.286
Take it.

03:23.286 --> 03:25.414
Yes, sir.
And thank you, sir.

03:25.414 --> 03:26.540
You're welcome.

03:27.124 --> 03:29.292
And Luna's okay with
you working Mother's Day?

03:29.292 --> 03:31.920
Yeah. It's the first year
Dominique's not at home.

03:31.920 --> 03:35.882
Luna said she's fine
keeping it super low-key.

03:35.882 --> 03:37.342
Oh.

03:37.342 --> 03:38.718
What?

03:40.554 --> 03:42.139
Do you think
she's just saying that?

03:42.139 --> 03:43.640
No.

03:43.640 --> 03:46.935
♪♪

03:46.935 --> 03:49.855
Lucy: Mm...yeah,
that's a hard pass.

03:49.855 --> 03:51.523
Look, I'm boycotting
Mother's Day,

03:51.523 --> 03:53.525
but even if I wasn't,
I really don't think this is

03:53.525 --> 03:55.152
the right time to meet
your parents.

03:55.152 --> 03:56.903
I figured you'd say that.

03:56.903 --> 03:58.947
But they've been
hounding me about

03:58.947 --> 04:01.032
meeting you for weeks.

04:01.032 --> 04:02.701
Are you really freezing
your mom out?

04:02.701 --> 04:05.871
I mean, I bought her flowers.
I'm not an anarchist.

04:05.871 --> 04:07.831
Tim: I'm thinking we just
lock in the Hyatt.

04:07.831 --> 04:09.374
They have a lazy river.
What else do you need?

04:09.374 --> 04:11.668
Great. You handle that,
I'll book the flights.

04:11.668 --> 04:12.711
On it.

04:12.711 --> 04:13.795
Are you guys planning
a vacation?

04:13.795 --> 04:16.089
Yeah. Hawaii.
Oh, I love Hawaii.

04:16.089 --> 04:18.592
Actually, I've never been,
but I love the idea.

04:18.592 --> 04:21.011
You'd think I'd be sick of
beaches at this point,

04:21.011 --> 04:23.346
but it's gonna be awesome.

04:23.346 --> 04:24.806
I've got to get to work.

04:24.806 --> 04:26.641
Oh, me, too.
I'll walk out with you.

04:26.641 --> 04:28.018
Call me if you
change your mind.

04:28.018 --> 04:30.187
I'm not going to.
Stop.

04:30.187 --> 04:31.646
Change your mind
about what?

04:31.646 --> 04:33.690
He wants me
to meet his parents.

04:33.690 --> 04:35.901
So, uh,
whose idea was Hawaii?

04:35.901 --> 04:38.278
Mine, I guess. Why?

04:38.278 --> 04:39.863
I-I thought
you had today off.

04:39.863 --> 04:42.741
I did, but Donovan
has custody this weekend,

04:42.741 --> 04:44.451
and he is punishing me
by taking Lila to see

04:44.451 --> 04:46.328
his mom
in Santa Barbara.

04:46.328 --> 04:49.623
So I am spending this
Mother's Day without my baby.

04:49.623 --> 04:51.708
Wow.
That is cruel, even for him.

04:51.708 --> 04:53.668
Yeah, I know.
And James is taking his boys

04:53.668 --> 04:55.670
to see his ex-wife,
because unlike Donovan,

04:55.670 --> 04:58.089
he is an actual
decent human being.

04:58.089 --> 05:01.510
But at least I get paid
time and a half to be here

05:01.510 --> 05:03.720
and plot my revenge.

05:03.720 --> 05:05.555
I can't wait to see
what you come up with.

05:05.555 --> 05:07.265
[ Chuckles ] Somebody
should sell tickets.

05:07.265 --> 05:08.225
Mm!

05:11.895 --> 05:13.563
Is it crazy I want to be
a T. O.

05:13.563 --> 05:14.898
with so little time
on the job?

05:14.898 --> 05:16.399
No.

05:16.399 --> 05:18.568
Your report writing
is excellent.

05:18.568 --> 05:20.445
You know policy, procedure,

05:20.445 --> 05:22.197
and the law well enough
to teach others.

05:22.197 --> 05:24.866
But your background
could be a drawback.

05:24.866 --> 05:27.619
Every other T. O. knows
what it's like to be a scared,

05:27.619 --> 05:30.747
20-something rookie
because they were one.

05:30.747 --> 05:32.791
And that shared experience
gives them the leg up

05:32.791 --> 05:33.834
in teaching that kid.

05:33.834 --> 05:34.960
Exactly.

05:34.960 --> 05:36.670
But your experiences
being a dad

05:36.670 --> 05:38.046
could help bridge
the gap.

05:38.046 --> 05:39.840
Only my kid was never
armed and dangerous.

05:43.385 --> 05:45.303
So, you really think
Luna's hoping

05:45.303 --> 05:47.430
that I do something big
for Mother's Day this year?

05:47.430 --> 05:50.392
I think it's always a safe bet
to go the extra mile.

05:53.270 --> 05:54.563
You're right.

05:54.563 --> 05:56.439
We should stop somewhere
so I can get a better gift.

05:56.439 --> 05:57.941
Yes, sir.
Yeah.

05:57.941 --> 05:59.317
Dispatch: <i>7-Adam-15.</i>

05:59.317 --> 06:01.820
<i>415 in progress</i>
<i>at Gower Studios.</i>

06:01.820 --> 06:03.196
Right after
we take this call.

06:03.196 --> 06:05.073
Yes, sir.
7-Adam-15.

06:05.073 --> 06:06.533
Show us responding.

06:06.533 --> 06:08.159
I don't know how many times
I need to say it.

06:08.159 --> 06:09.536
Please clean it up, okay?

06:09.536 --> 06:10.787
I'm actually triggered by this,
you guys.

06:10.787 --> 06:11.872
I don't think you understand.

06:11.872 --> 06:13.164
They're here. See?
[ Gasps ]

06:13.164 --> 06:14.875
Oh, Sergeant.

06:14.875 --> 06:15.959
Thank God you're here.

06:15.959 --> 06:16.960
Ms. Fowler.

06:16.960 --> 06:18.378
Sabrina Fowler.

06:18.378 --> 06:20.046
She's an actress on
"Hot Suspect."

06:20.046 --> 06:21.381
I'm pretty sure
he knows that.

06:21.381 --> 06:22.716
It's nice to meet you.

06:22.716 --> 06:24.301
Congratulations on
the baby.

06:24.301 --> 06:25.635
Unless it's just
for the show.

06:25.635 --> 06:27.053
Oh, it's both.

06:27.053 --> 06:28.471
They made
my character pregnant,

06:28.471 --> 06:30.473
so I got pregnant
in real life.

06:30.473 --> 06:32.183
Because she's
a method actor.

06:32.183 --> 06:34.978
How else am I gonna
understand the experience?

06:35.854 --> 06:37.856
Wow.

06:37.856 --> 06:39.691
So, what happened here,
exactly?

06:39.691 --> 06:40.901
We got a call
about an assault?

06:40.901 --> 06:44.404
That's right. The girl from
crafty assaulted me...

06:44.404 --> 06:46.364
with a crouton.

06:46.364 --> 06:47.365
She threw it at you?

06:47.365 --> 06:49.367
No.
She put it in my salad.

06:49.951 --> 06:51.828
Do you know how many carbs
are in a crouton?

06:53.413 --> 06:56.458
Right. Um, well,
what was the name of your,

06:56.458 --> 06:58.710
uh...attacker?

06:58.710 --> 07:00.920
Mm, salad girl?
I don't...

07:00.920 --> 07:03.006
No. Wait. I heard somebody
call her Monica

07:03.006 --> 07:04.799
while she was
destroying everything.

07:04.799 --> 07:06.176
So she made this mess.
That's right.

07:06.176 --> 07:07.302
She completely
freaked out

07:07.302 --> 07:08.637
when I told her I was
gonna have her fired.

07:08.637 --> 07:10.930
For putting a crouton
on your salad?

07:10.930 --> 07:12.307
Are you taking her side?

07:12.307 --> 07:14.434
Of course not.
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

07:14.434 --> 07:15.977
Excuse me.
I have to take this.

07:15.977 --> 07:17.020
The D. A.'s office.

07:17.020 --> 07:18.647
Tell them I'm okay.
I am okay.

07:18.647 --> 07:20.732
I will still make it to court
for the Sanchez trial.

07:21.900 --> 07:24.903
[ Sighs ] I'm prosecuting
a serial killer later.

07:24.903 --> 07:26.363
Oh. On the show.
Right.

07:26.363 --> 07:27.781
But that was actually
the real...

07:29.949 --> 07:31.409
You know what?
Never mind.

07:31.409 --> 07:33.244
Is there anything else you can
tell me about the incident?

07:33.244 --> 07:35.497
Like six people recorded it
on their phones.

07:35.497 --> 07:37.332
We're trending
on Cliptalk.

07:37.332 --> 07:38.375
Right.

07:38.375 --> 07:39.959
They're calling <i>her</i>
a folk hero.

07:39.959 --> 07:42.545
Can you believe it?
As if <i>I'm</i> the bad guy.

07:42.545 --> 07:44.005
We're needed elsewhere.

07:44.005 --> 07:46.007
Ms. Fowler, I'm gonna have
a unit reach out

07:46.007 --> 07:48.843
to studio security to get
your attacker's information.

07:49.719 --> 07:51.429
I want the book
thrown at her.

07:51.429 --> 07:52.430
Of course.

07:52.430 --> 07:53.973
And happy Mother's Day.

07:53.973 --> 07:56.559
Oh, thank you.
[ Laughs ]

07:57.268 --> 07:58.561
Nice fake phone call.

07:58.561 --> 07:59.854
It wasn't fake.

07:59.854 --> 08:02.232
The D. A.'s office has
a witness to secure,

08:02.232 --> 08:05.068
and they asked for an advanced
team to assess the site.

08:05.068 --> 08:07.612
So I guess Luna's present will
have to wait a while longer?

08:07.612 --> 08:09.280
[ Sighs ]

08:09.280 --> 08:11.324
Yeah, but don't
let me forget.

08:13.410 --> 08:15.120
[ Police radio chatter ]

08:18.873 --> 08:21.584
Are you proposing
to Ashley?

08:21.584 --> 08:23.420
What?

08:23.420 --> 08:24.671
Of course not.

08:24.671 --> 08:26.381
We -- We've only been
dating a few months.

08:26.381 --> 08:28.383
Okay.

08:28.383 --> 08:30.009
But if you take
a girl to Hawaii,

08:30.009 --> 08:31.761
there's gonna
be expectations.

08:31.761 --> 08:34.264
You might not be aware
of some of the signals
that you're sending.

08:34.264 --> 08:35.432
What kind of signals?

08:35.432 --> 08:37.100
The kind that makes her get
a manicure because

08:37.100 --> 08:39.144
she's assuming she'll be
sending pictures of her hand

08:39.144 --> 08:40.562
to all her friends.

08:41.771 --> 08:43.481
Dispatch: <i>7-Adam-100.</i>

08:43.481 --> 08:45.150
<i>What's your status?</i>

08:45.150 --> 08:47.068
Uh, 7-Adam-100.

08:47.068 --> 08:49.237
Show us
Code 6 on our 415.

08:49.237 --> 08:50.822
-They lost her keys.
-Where are my keys?

08:50.822 --> 08:52.824
Sir, please.
You lost my Bentley.

08:52.824 --> 08:55.410
No, sir, I just -- I just don't
know where the keys are.

08:55.410 --> 08:57.120
Okay, everyone, just calm down.
Back up a little bit, please.

08:57.120 --> 08:58.246
Thank you.

08:58.246 --> 09:00.081
What's going on?
Jonah went crazy.

09:00.081 --> 09:01.666
He punched that guy
in the face,

09:01.666 --> 09:04.252
and he emptied the key cabinet
and then stole a car.

09:04.252 --> 09:06.796
Patrol, we need an R. A. at our
location for an assault victim.

09:06.796 --> 09:08.423
Jonah is a valet?

09:08.423 --> 09:10.425
Yeah, yeah.
He just started last week.

09:10.425 --> 09:12.510
At first, he was amused
by all the rich guests.

09:12.510 --> 09:14.179
You know how petty
and demanding they are.

09:14.179 --> 09:15.722
No offense.

09:15.722 --> 09:18.058
But when that dude told him to
move his ass, he snapped.

09:18.058 --> 09:19.809
Knocked the guy out,
jumped into his Porsche,

09:19.809 --> 09:21.978
and took off with
all the car keys.

09:21.978 --> 09:24.147
And what color
is the Porsche?

09:24.147 --> 09:26.274
Wesley: So all you did was reach
inside of an open car window

09:26.274 --> 09:28.526
and take a bag of chips
from the passenger seat.

09:28.526 --> 09:29.652
Yes.

09:29.652 --> 09:31.863
I was super hungry,
and it was right there.

09:31.863 --> 09:32.906
[ Jack fusses ]

09:32.906 --> 09:35.283
Are you allowed to bring
a baby in here?

09:36.117 --> 09:37.577
Oh, he's my intern.

09:37.577 --> 09:39.829
So, why is the District Attorney
adding these extra charges?

09:39.829 --> 09:41.623
Burglary
and vehicle tampering.

09:41.623 --> 09:43.792
You're looking at the one
who <i>didn't</i> go to law school.

09:43.792 --> 09:45.168
I have no idea.

09:45.168 --> 09:46.503
[ Sighs ]

09:46.503 --> 09:48.838
The ADA in charge of your case
is Philip Harmon.

09:48.838 --> 09:51.800
He's notorious for
up-charging defendants.

09:51.800 --> 09:53.384
Is there anything
you can do about it?

09:53.384 --> 09:55.845
[ Sighs ]
Uh...not much.

09:55.845 --> 09:57.514
He does it to force you
to take a plea deal

09:57.514 --> 09:58.598
while he looks
tough on crime.

09:58.598 --> 10:00.475
That doesn't seem fair.

10:01.726 --> 10:02.977
It's not.

10:02.977 --> 10:05.021
I'll get right into this.
Hang tight.

10:05.021 --> 10:06.606
Come on, buddy.
Thanks.

10:07.148 --> 10:10.235
If you want, I could watch
the baby while you work.

10:10.235 --> 10:13.571
Not sure how my wife would feel
about that, but thank you.

10:13.571 --> 10:15.365
[ Chuckles ]
Come on, buddy.

10:15.365 --> 10:16.783
[ Jack fusses ]

10:17.784 --> 10:18.910
[ Door opens ]

10:18.910 --> 10:21.412
[ Classical music playing ]

10:21.412 --> 10:25.583
No breakfast in bed, but Wesley
did get me this bracelet.

10:26.668 --> 10:27.919
That's lovely.

10:27.919 --> 10:30.130
It's no diamond
tennis bracelet,

10:30.130 --> 10:32.173
but I don't need him
to show me his love

10:32.173 --> 10:33.424
with extravagant gifts.

10:33.424 --> 10:36.261
Well, no one needs it,
but wouldn't it be nice?

10:36.261 --> 10:37.637
[ Cellphone chimes ]

10:39.013 --> 10:40.598
Wesley's running
even later.

10:40.598 --> 10:42.016
Oh.
We should order.

10:42.016 --> 10:43.518
It's probably
for the best.

10:43.518 --> 10:45.520
Rich-people stuff isn't
as fun when he's around.

10:45.520 --> 10:48.773
[ Chuckles ] No, he does tend
to dampen the mood.

10:48.773 --> 10:51.442
How about you and I spend
the afternoon shopping?

10:51.442 --> 10:53.194
I'll hire a driver,

10:53.194 --> 10:55.363
and we'll do your
first Mother's Day right.

10:55.363 --> 10:57.282
I love you.

10:57.282 --> 10:59.117
Yes.
Cheers to that.

10:59.117 --> 11:00.368
Cheers.

11:00.785 --> 11:01.953
[ Gunshot ]

11:01.953 --> 11:04.330
Jonah: Good morning,
and happy Mother's Day.

11:04.330 --> 11:06.791
Now, I hate to interrupt
your little manufactured

11:06.791 --> 11:09.669
family gathering,
but this is a robbery.

11:09.669 --> 11:12.005
Let's go.
Everyone stay calm
and you won't get hurt.

11:12.005 --> 11:14.215
Just put all your belongings
in the bag.

11:14.215 --> 11:15.383
What are you gonna do?

11:15.383 --> 11:16.676
Stay calm.
Do as they say.

11:16.676 --> 11:18.011
We don't want to make
the situation worse.

11:18.011 --> 11:19.929
Come on,
cough it up, ladies.

11:19.929 --> 11:22.223
Monica: Yeah.
That's beautiful.

11:22.223 --> 11:23.516
Thank you.

11:23.516 --> 11:25.977
[ Gun cocks ]
Give me the pearls.

11:25.977 --> 11:28.188
[ Clears throat ]
Please.

11:28.188 --> 11:29.439
My late husband
gave me --

11:29.439 --> 11:30.690
I don't care.

11:30.690 --> 11:32.692
Put it in the bag before
I rip it off your neck.

11:32.692 --> 11:35.236
Patrice, we'll
get it back, okay?

11:35.236 --> 11:36.696
♪ If you tryna keep up,
better run, I guess ♪

11:36.696 --> 11:38.656
You know, you really shouldn't
lie to your elders.

11:38.656 --> 11:41.075
I'm not lying
when I tell her that.

11:41.075 --> 11:44.996
Or when I tell you
you're under arrest.

11:44.996 --> 11:46.831
[ Laughs ]

11:46.831 --> 11:48.333
You know,
I love the confidence.

11:48.333 --> 11:51.753
But, uh...we're the only ones
with guns here.

11:51.753 --> 11:53.296
Oh, I don't mean now.

11:53.296 --> 11:56.216
But soon enough, we'll
be putting a different
kind of bracelet on you.

11:56.216 --> 11:58.051
[ Laughs ]

11:58.051 --> 12:01.095
♪ It's mine for the taking,
it's mine for the taking ♪

12:01.095 --> 12:02.889
Thank you!
Monica: Whoo!

12:02.889 --> 12:04.766
I'll take that.

12:04.766 --> 12:06.184
Yeah, baby!
♪ I am the greatest ♪

12:06.184 --> 12:07.477
Thanks, everybody!
We love you!

12:10.438 --> 12:11.981
♪ You better bow down
when you see the queen ♪

12:11.981 --> 12:13.191
Hey. You okay?

12:13.191 --> 12:15.026
Yeah.
Did Wesley find you?

12:15.026 --> 12:16.194
He's been frantic.

12:16.194 --> 12:17.362
I know.

12:17.362 --> 12:19.364
Patrice and I had to
scrape him off the ceiling.

12:19.364 --> 12:21.866
I sent him and Jack away
so I could go to work.

12:21.866 --> 12:23.117
Did you get an I. D.
on the stick-up team?

12:23.117 --> 12:25.787
Yep. Jonah Cahill,
Monica Ditmar.

12:25.787 --> 12:27.413
That's our valet.

12:27.413 --> 12:29.624
He beat up a guest this morning
and stole a Porsche.

12:29.624 --> 12:31.501
Oh, and that's the woman
that Nolan and Grey

12:31.501 --> 12:32.710
put out a BOLO for.

12:32.710 --> 12:34.587
She pitched a fit
at one of the stars

12:34.587 --> 12:36.005
on "Hot Suspect"
and then quit.

12:36.005 --> 12:38.299
Which suggests the robbery was
a spur-of-the-moment thing.

12:38.299 --> 12:40.885
Yeah. They might have
snapped after a bad morning

12:40.885 --> 12:42.720
at work and decided
that crime paid better.

12:42.720 --> 12:44.514
I'm assuming they
have criminal records?

12:44.514 --> 12:48.059
Yeah. Minor offenses stretching
back into their teens.

12:48.059 --> 12:50.395
They're both living at
a halfway house in Koreatown.

12:50.395 --> 12:52.939
I got uniforms parked outside
in case they come back.

12:52.939 --> 12:54.899
They stole your
Mother's Day's present?

12:54.899 --> 12:56.317
I'm going to get it back.

12:56.317 --> 12:58.152
Damn right you are.
And I am gonna help you.

12:58.152 --> 13:00.321
Nobody messes with Mother's Day
and gets away with it.

13:00.321 --> 13:01.614
♪ For the war, for the war ♪

13:01.614 --> 13:03.533
Donovan took
Lila out of town.

13:03.533 --> 13:04.742
What?
Mm-hmm.

13:04.742 --> 13:07.662
I knew he was an ass, but
I didn't think he was evil.

13:07.662 --> 13:11.124
My abuela taught me the perfect
curse to put on him.

13:11.124 --> 13:13.584
Ooh!
Does it involve boils?

13:13.584 --> 13:16.379
No, but parts of him
will definitely fall off.

13:16.379 --> 13:17.880
Ooh!
Okay, we should leave before

13:17.880 --> 13:20.049
we become accessories.
Mm-hmm.

13:20.049 --> 13:22.260
Those robbers
don't stand a chance.

13:22.260 --> 13:25.138
[ Siren wailing ]

13:28.516 --> 13:30.727
Here we are.

13:30.727 --> 13:33.021
The Royal Arms apartments.

13:33.021 --> 13:34.731
D.A.'s office is gonna
secure their witness here

13:34.731 --> 13:36.983
for a week while they get
a more permanent situation

13:36.983 --> 13:38.276
put in place.

13:38.276 --> 13:39.986
That must be tough
going into WITSEC.

13:39.986 --> 13:41.612
I mean, I changed my whole
life to come out here,

13:41.612 --> 13:43.906
but I didn't have to
cut ties with my family.

13:43.906 --> 13:45.116
This poor guy's gonna
have to give up

13:45.116 --> 13:46.451
everything
he's ever known.

13:46.451 --> 13:49.203
This "poor guy" is
a runner for a street gang.

13:49.203 --> 13:51.539
He stood by and watched
people get murdered.

13:51.539 --> 13:53.666
He's lucky his testimony
is valuable enough

13:53.666 --> 13:55.084
to get him immunity.

13:55.084 --> 13:56.878
So, what do we have to do
to get the site prepped

13:56.878 --> 13:58.087
for witness protection?

13:58.087 --> 14:01.132
First, the C.I. needs to be
given clear boundaries,

14:01.132 --> 14:04.594
the landmarks that he cannot
cross, to keep him isolated.

14:04.594 --> 14:07.305
Okay, how about Sixth Street
to the north,

14:07.305 --> 14:08.765
that grocery store
to the south?

14:08.765 --> 14:10.266
That way, there's lots
of cameras and witnesses

14:10.266 --> 14:11.476
in case
anything happens.

14:11.476 --> 14:13.269
That's perfect.

14:13.269 --> 14:15.146
Let's go check out
this apartment.

14:18.024 --> 14:19.817
Looks like nobody's been
here in a while.

14:19.817 --> 14:21.986
Still have to
clear it anyway.

14:23.863 --> 14:27.200
Okay. Search for cameras
and listening devices.

14:27.200 --> 14:28.659
[ Beep ]
Hold the button down,

14:28.659 --> 14:32.330
wave it over anything
that may hide a bug.

14:32.330 --> 14:33.498
Gotcha.

14:33.498 --> 14:35.333
[ Siren wailing in distance ]

14:35.333 --> 14:37.210
What was your FTO like?

14:37.210 --> 14:38.586
[ Chuckles ]

14:38.586 --> 14:40.296
He was one of those guys
who thought he could

14:40.296 --> 14:42.381
motivate me
with threats.

14:42.381 --> 14:44.675
One night, he drove me
behind the grocery store,

14:44.675 --> 14:47.553
took off his belt and vest,
and wanted to fight.

14:47.553 --> 14:48.638
What did you do?

14:48.638 --> 14:50.473
I put him
in the hospital.

14:50.473 --> 14:52.350
He tread a lot more carefully
after that.

14:52.350 --> 14:53.476
I bet he did.

14:53.476 --> 14:55.561
[ Chuckles ]
Check the bedroom.

14:57.688 --> 15:00.149
There's four types of
training officers --

15:00.149 --> 15:03.528
Kings, Coaches,
Teachers, and Slugs.

15:03.528 --> 15:05.613
Well, I already know
the Slug one.

15:05.613 --> 15:08.616
That one's just doing it
for the pay bump.

15:08.616 --> 15:11.536
Kings are the
"my way or the highway" type.

15:11.536 --> 15:13.412
Coaches offer motivation,

15:13.412 --> 15:15.414
and Teachers always want to
explain everything.

15:15.414 --> 15:17.625
Which of the categories
do I fit under?

15:17.625 --> 15:19.293
None.

15:19.293 --> 15:21.212
That's why you got the potential
to make a great T. O.

15:21.212 --> 15:23.840
Take the best qualities of
all the leaders and trainers

15:23.840 --> 15:26.342
who shaped who you
are as a cop,

15:26.342 --> 15:27.927
and you'll make
your own category.

15:31.556 --> 15:32.765
[ <i>Ringing</i> ]

15:32.765 --> 15:35.768
[ Ringing ]
Del Monte.

15:35.768 --> 15:37.103
Site's secure.

15:37.103 --> 15:38.688
So, you need us
to hang around?

15:38.688 --> 15:40.606
'Cause I got a Mother's Day
present to buy.

15:40.606 --> 15:42.525
Oh, it's a little late
for that, isn't it?

15:42.525 --> 15:43.860
Yeah.

15:43.860 --> 15:45.403
Yeah, actually, I would
appreciate you hanging out.

15:45.403 --> 15:47.238
<i>Uh, my guy is super twitchy.</i>

15:47.238 --> 15:49.240
Having you there play the heavy
will definitely help

15:49.240 --> 15:50.449
him play by the rules,
you know?

15:50.449 --> 15:51.993
No problem.

15:51.993 --> 15:56.497
♪♪

15:56.497 --> 15:58.374
[ Sighs ]

16:01.002 --> 16:02.712
[ Jack fusses ]
Hey, Sean.

16:02.712 --> 16:03.629
Got a minute?

16:03.629 --> 16:05.256
Uh, yeah, one.

16:05.256 --> 16:06.507
[ Jack laughs ]

16:06.507 --> 16:08.050
Cute kid.

16:08.050 --> 16:10.887
Oh, hey, you're working
on Lopez's first Mother's Day.

16:10.887 --> 16:12.555
[ Chuckles ] Brave man.

16:12.555 --> 16:14.515
Yeah, in my defense,
she's working, too.

16:14.515 --> 16:16.893
She and my mom were robbed
at brunch.

16:16.893 --> 16:18.561
Yeah, I heard about that.
Everybody okay?

16:18.561 --> 16:20.188
Yeah. Thank God.

16:20.188 --> 16:21.898
I should have been there,
but I was dealing with

16:21.898 --> 16:25.276
yet another case of
prosecutorial overreach.

16:25.276 --> 16:26.569
[ Chuckles ]

16:26.569 --> 16:28.571
Well, if that's your way of
buttering me up for a favor,

16:28.571 --> 16:29.655
you might want
to rethink it.

16:29.655 --> 16:31.282
Gemma Ramp stole
a bag of potato chips,

16:31.282 --> 16:32.658
you guys are charging her
with a felony?

16:32.658 --> 16:34.368
Oh, yeah, no, that's not mine.
That's Harmon's.

16:34.368 --> 16:36.078
I know.
Hoping you'd talk to him.

16:36.078 --> 16:40.124
Yeah, I mean, I can,
but it's not gonna matter.

16:40.124 --> 16:41.876
That's just his way
of doing business.

16:41.876 --> 16:43.419
Come on, Wes.
None of this is new.

16:43.419 --> 16:45.421
I know.

16:45.421 --> 16:47.882
It just seems like things
are only getting worse.

16:49.800 --> 16:52.178
Look, you're not wrong.

16:52.178 --> 16:56.098
But to be honest,
I'm surrounded by lawyers

16:56.098 --> 16:57.808
who think that being
tough on crime

16:57.808 --> 16:59.560
is gonna get them
the top job.

16:59.560 --> 17:01.729
Hell, I've been
vetting candidates for
Kelly's open spot,

17:01.729 --> 17:03.314
and each one is
more gung ho than the last.

17:03.314 --> 17:04.815
I get it.

17:04.815 --> 17:08.402
My client is steps away
from the street.

17:08.402 --> 17:12.323
She needs a break,
not the book thrown at her.

17:12.323 --> 17:14.325
I get it. I do.

17:14.325 --> 17:16.369
I just -- There's nothing
I can do about it.

17:16.369 --> 17:17.703
My hands are tied.
I'm sorry.

17:17.703 --> 17:19.163
I gotta run.

17:19.163 --> 17:25.419
♪♪

17:25.419 --> 17:26.921
I already know
what you're gonna say.

17:26.921 --> 17:28.965
My mother's just trying to do
what's best for me.

17:28.965 --> 17:30.967
Oh, no.

17:30.967 --> 17:33.719
Your mom sounds like
a real piece of work.

17:34.804 --> 17:37.348
It's not your job
to make amends.

17:37.348 --> 17:39.433
It's hers.

17:39.433 --> 17:41.435
[ Chuckles ]
Thank you so much.

17:41.435 --> 17:42.812
I...
Yeah.

17:42.812 --> 17:45.815
Okay, when did hotels
get so expensive?

17:45.815 --> 17:47.608
Hi.
Hi, Tim.

17:47.608 --> 17:49.819
Oh, that's pretty good.
Seriously?

17:49.819 --> 17:51.946
Yeah. I mean,
it's a nice hotel.

17:51.946 --> 17:53.322
If you want to do
better than that,

17:53.322 --> 17:56.367
you're gonna have to take
Ashley to Honolulu Motel 6.

17:56.367 --> 17:57.952
Oh,
you're going to Hawaii.

17:57.952 --> 18:00.538
[ Gasps ] Congratulations
on your engagement.

18:00.538 --> 18:02.039
Ah! Told you.

18:02.039 --> 18:03.416
I'm not getting engaged.

18:03.416 --> 18:05.001
Does your girlfriend
know that?

18:05.001 --> 18:06.752
Yes.
It's not an issue.

18:06.752 --> 18:08.588
[ Chuckles ]
Is he really this clueless?

18:08.588 --> 18:12.675
Yes, trust me.
It is a daily struggle.

18:12.675 --> 18:14.093
Let's go.

18:14.093 --> 18:15.303
Lopez: <i>You've reached</i>
<i>the cellphone of</i>

18:15.303 --> 18:16.679
<i>Detective Angela Lopez.</i>

18:16.679 --> 18:17.763
<i>Leave a message.</i>

18:17.763 --> 18:19.181
[ Beep ]
Any luck?

18:19.181 --> 18:21.225
[ Sighs ] No.

18:21.225 --> 18:25.229
I called half the phones
they stole, including mine.

18:25.229 --> 18:26.480
Straight to voicemail.

18:26.480 --> 18:28.190
I've got plainclothes
officers stationed

18:28.190 --> 18:29.900
at all of the pawnshops
this side of the 405.

18:29.900 --> 18:31.902
If they show up,
we will be waiting.

18:31.902 --> 18:34.238
Tell them I want to be the one
who puts on the cuffs.

18:34.238 --> 18:36.073
[ <i>Ringing</i> ]
I made a promise.

18:36.073 --> 18:38.117
[ Cellphone rings ]
I love it so much.

18:38.117 --> 18:40.328
New phone, who dis?

18:40.328 --> 18:41.579
[ <i>Both laugh</i> ]

18:41.579 --> 18:44.540
Detective Lopez.
We met this morning.

18:44.540 --> 18:46.250
It's the cop
from the restaurant.

18:46.250 --> 18:47.752
What's up, Detective?

18:47.752 --> 18:49.378
You, uh,
calling to arrest us?

18:49.378 --> 18:51.005
'Cause I don't think you can
do that over the phone.

18:51.005 --> 18:52.298
[ Laughs ]

18:52.298 --> 18:54.383
No, I'm calling to tell you
to turn yourselves in.

18:54.383 --> 18:55.885
You committed
armed robbery.

18:55.885 --> 18:57.553
Half the LAPD
is looking for you.

18:57.553 --> 18:59.305
Yeah, that's not
gonna happen.

18:59.305 --> 19:00.973
See, we've got this whole
crime spree planned out.

19:00.973 --> 19:02.224
Isn't that right, baby?
That's right.

19:02.224 --> 19:04.685
Listen, I know you two
have gone through a lot.

19:04.685 --> 19:07.396
Please. If you think reading
a file gives you any idea

19:07.396 --> 19:09.106
who we are,
you are a terrible cop.

19:09.106 --> 19:11.317
Trust me, I've read enough
files to understand

19:11.317 --> 19:13.444
that you and Jonah never
caught a single break.

19:13.444 --> 19:15.613
[ Cellphone chimes ]
Yet, when you got out of prison,

19:15.613 --> 19:18.366
you tried to go straight,
even got yourselves real jobs.

19:18.366 --> 19:21.160
Yeah. And you know what?
We were still treated like scum.

19:21.160 --> 19:23.162
Not even worth
an ounce of respect.

19:23.162 --> 19:25.623
Angela, they are live-streaming
your conversation.

19:25.623 --> 19:27.792
<i>You can save</i>
<i>the false empathy, Detective.</i>

19:27.792 --> 19:30.961
<i>Today is for every worker</i>
<i>who's ever been mistreated...</i>

19:30.961 --> 19:32.213
<i>Mm.</i>
<i>...for anyone who's ever</i>

19:32.213 --> 19:33.422
<i>wanted to walk off the job.</i>

19:33.422 --> 19:35.174
<i>Yeah, for anybody that</i>
<i>believed the lie</i>

19:35.174 --> 19:36.884
<i>that if you just tried</i>
<i>to work harder,</i>

19:36.884 --> 19:38.260
<i>you could achieve</i>
<i>your dreams.</i>

19:38.260 --> 19:40.304
We are done
begging for scraps.

19:40.304 --> 19:43.140
Today, we are taking
what's ours.

19:43.140 --> 19:44.809
Let's take it all, baby.

19:44.809 --> 19:46.268
We are taking it.

19:46.268 --> 19:47.395
<i>Let's take it all.</i>

19:47.395 --> 19:48.688
♪ Any point that you made ♪

19:48.688 --> 19:50.356
<i>I love you.</i>
<i>I love you.</i>

19:56.320 --> 19:59.240
Man, I don't like this place.
It's claustrophobic.

19:59.240 --> 20:00.491
Mr. Tran...

20:00.491 --> 20:03.661
Is it just me,
or is it dusty up in here?

20:03.661 --> 20:05.079
I feel like
I can't breathe.

20:05.079 --> 20:06.247
Daniel, sit down.

20:06.247 --> 20:07.623
[ Siren wailing
in distance ]

20:07.623 --> 20:09.333
If you want to stay alive,
you need to listen to what

20:09.333 --> 20:10.876
Mr. Del Monte
has to say.

20:10.876 --> 20:12.294
Nolan: Thank you.

20:12.294 --> 20:14.338
As an informant
in our protection program,

20:14.338 --> 20:16.674
there are a number of rules
that you will follow.

20:16.674 --> 20:19.093
You will not disclose
this location to anybody.

20:19.093 --> 20:21.554
Do you understand?
Good.

20:21.554 --> 20:23.055
This is your new phone.

20:23.055 --> 20:25.808
Do not share this number
with anybody.

20:25.808 --> 20:27.893
Officer Nolan
and Sergeant Grey

20:27.893 --> 20:30.146
have established
a strict perimeter in the area.

20:30.146 --> 20:32.523
This is a boundary
that you will not cross

20:32.523 --> 20:34.150
under any circumstances.

20:34.150 --> 20:35.526
Is that clear?

20:35.526 --> 20:37.778
But I can visit my mom,
right?

20:37.778 --> 20:40.614
No. Daniel...

20:40.614 --> 20:43.576
you are not to contact
any friends or family, period.

20:43.576 --> 20:45.161
But it's Mother's Day.

20:45.161 --> 20:46.704
We're going
horseback riding later.

20:46.704 --> 20:48.706
Son, you're clearly
not understanding

20:48.706 --> 20:51.083
the severity
of the situation.

20:51.083 --> 20:54.503
You will not contact anyone,
family included.

20:54.503 --> 20:57.006
But I have to.
I can't let her down again.

20:57.006 --> 20:59.925
Look, this is for
her safety, too.

20:59.925 --> 21:02.887
Okay, if you really want
to see your mom,

21:02.887 --> 21:05.181
I'm sure we can arrange to
have you both meet

21:05.181 --> 21:06.348
in a secure location.

21:06.348 --> 21:07.516
You can say your goodbyes.

21:07.516 --> 21:09.351
Goodbyes? No.

21:09.351 --> 21:11.353
Daniel, this is
your reality now.

21:11.353 --> 21:12.688
I know it's not pretty,

21:12.688 --> 21:15.316
but it's the only way we can
keep you alive.

21:20.154 --> 21:21.405
Del Monte:
Alright, thanks, guys.

21:21.405 --> 21:22.865
We'll take it from here.
Appreciate it.

21:22.865 --> 21:24.909
Present time?
Yeah.

21:24.909 --> 21:27.244
Only I have absolutely
no idea what to get her.

21:27.244 --> 21:28.954
Well, lucky enough,
we got four hours

21:28.954 --> 21:30.247
to figure something out.

21:30.247 --> 21:32.041
Lopez: I got an update
on Monica and Jonah.

21:32.041 --> 21:33.709
They just robbed
a bridal store.

21:33.709 --> 21:34.960
That's an odd choice.

21:34.960 --> 21:37.546
They assaulted the owner
and held her at gunpoint

21:37.546 --> 21:39.048
while Monica
tried on dresses.

21:39.048 --> 21:41.926
Oh, well, I guess you won't
be the only one getting married.

21:41.926 --> 21:42.968
What?

21:42.968 --> 21:44.720
Nothing. Ignore her.

21:44.720 --> 21:46.889
We need to catch these two
before they kill somebody.

21:46.889 --> 21:49.350
Well, given the fact that they
made off with a dress and tux,

21:49.350 --> 21:50.935
odds are they're
about to get hitched.

21:50.935 --> 21:52.228
Alright.
We'll alert the local venues

21:52.228 --> 21:54.063
and check out
the obvious locations.

21:56.065 --> 21:57.566
Okay, I'm starting to
panic a little.

21:57.566 --> 21:59.610
Luna and I have been
married 25 years.

21:59.610 --> 22:01.654
At this point, I've given her
every kind of present there is.

22:03.614 --> 22:05.407
So how do I make
this one special?

22:05.407 --> 22:08.077
Well, maybe don't
make it about the present.

22:08.077 --> 22:09.203
Make it about
the evening.

22:09.203 --> 22:11.455
What's her
favorite restaurant?

22:11.455 --> 22:13.290
Do you think I can
get a reservation

22:13.290 --> 22:14.542
anywhere at this point?

22:14.542 --> 22:15.709
Ooh.
No, not a chance in hell.

22:15.709 --> 22:16.877
[ Cellphone rings ]

22:16.877 --> 22:19.088
[ Scoffs ]
Sean, what's up?

22:20.256 --> 22:22.758
No, we're on it.
[ Sighs ]

22:22.758 --> 22:24.093
Daniel Tran took off.

22:24.093 --> 22:25.803
That was fast.
Yeah.

22:25.803 --> 22:27.721
Lucky for us, we know
exactly where he's heading.

22:27.721 --> 22:30.432
Oh! According to this
travel website,

22:30.432 --> 22:33.561
Siberia is the least romantic
place to vacation.

22:35.479 --> 22:38.274
I am not rerouting our trip
to the arctic tundra

22:38.274 --> 22:40.818
because you think Hawaii
sends the wrong message.

22:40.818 --> 22:43.070
No, it is
not just me, okay?

22:43.070 --> 22:46.657
TouristPlanet says that
Hawaii is number one

22:46.657 --> 22:48.909
for proposals in 2021.

22:48.909 --> 22:51.495
Ashley can't possibly
think I'm proposing.

22:51.495 --> 22:52.496
Why not?

22:52.496 --> 22:55.332
I mean, you're of
a...certain age.

22:55.332 --> 22:56.750
She's in her prime.

22:56.750 --> 23:00.170
I mean, on paper, it's --
it's like a no-brainer.

23:00.170 --> 23:01.714
Okay, be honest.

23:03.132 --> 23:05.426
Can you see yourself
married to her?

23:10.764 --> 23:12.308
Yeah.

23:12.308 --> 23:13.517
I can.

23:19.732 --> 23:21.025
Dispatch: <i>7-Adam-100.</i>

23:21.025 --> 23:22.610
<i>I have a 415 unknown</i>
<i>in progress</i>

23:22.610 --> 23:24.028
<i>at Church of the Chimes.</i>

23:24.028 --> 23:25.195
That's gotta be Jonah
and Monica.

23:25.195 --> 23:26.780
[ Siren wailing ]
Show us responding.

23:26.780 --> 23:29.533
Send backup, metro,
and alert Detective Lopez.

23:29.533 --> 23:30.659
[ Wagner's "Bridal Chorus"
playing ]

23:30.659 --> 23:33.996
Jonah: Hey, hey!
Hey, everyone. Be cool.

23:33.996 --> 23:35.623
You can get back to your wedding
in a few minutes.

23:35.623 --> 23:38.083
We wrote our own vows,
so if anybody ruins them,

23:38.083 --> 23:39.501
they catch a bullet,
understand?

23:39.501 --> 23:42.630
H-Hey, hey, hey. And you --
And if you screw up this video,

23:42.630 --> 23:45.215
it'll mean a world
of pain, alright?

23:45.215 --> 23:48.886
[ Music continues ]

23:48.886 --> 23:51.305
[ Breathes deeply ]

23:51.305 --> 23:55.100
Baby, you are
the love of my life.

23:55.100 --> 23:57.478
Before I met you,
I hated the world.

23:57.478 --> 24:00.105
But now...

24:00.105 --> 24:03.776
Now we can hate the world
together forever.

24:03.776 --> 24:07.780
Jonah...you're
my ride or die,

24:07.780 --> 24:10.532
the only person who
has ever really seen me.

24:11.784 --> 24:13.494
No matter what
happens next,

24:13.494 --> 24:15.913
you've made me
the happiest girl...

24:21.377 --> 24:22.795
[ People screaming ]

24:22.795 --> 24:24.838
Jonah!
Jonah, we gotta go.

24:24.838 --> 24:26.215
Hey, are we
officially married?

24:26.215 --> 24:27.132
Yes!

24:27.132 --> 24:28.801
♪♪

24:28.801 --> 24:30.052
Ah!

24:30.052 --> 24:32.262
7-Adam-100.
Shots fired at our location.

24:32.262 --> 24:34.181
Pursuing armed suspects
on foot.

24:34.181 --> 24:35.766
We need backup
at all exits.

24:35.766 --> 24:36.934
Tim: Go, go.
Go to the back.

24:36.934 --> 24:38.060
Go. Exit.

24:38.060 --> 24:39.436
Move, move.

24:39.436 --> 24:41.814
♪ Hold on to your genre ♪

24:41.814 --> 24:44.108
♪ Your genre's got
a hold on you ♪

24:45.150 --> 24:47.403
♪ Hold on to your hairdo ♪

24:47.403 --> 24:50.906
♪ It's the only thing
to hold on to ♪

24:50.906 --> 24:52.700
[ Door opens ]

24:52.700 --> 24:58.455
♪♪

24:58.455 --> 25:00.833
[ Groans, coughs ]

25:00.833 --> 25:07.840
♪♪

25:07.840 --> 25:10.092
[ Groaning ]

25:11.010 --> 25:12.594
No, no.

25:12.594 --> 25:13.762
No, no, no, no, no.

25:13.762 --> 25:15.264
You gotta leave me.

25:15.264 --> 25:16.432
No.

25:16.432 --> 25:17.933
If you leave right now,
you could save yourself.

25:17.933 --> 25:19.435
No.
You could just --

25:19.435 --> 25:20.894
just break me
out of jail.

25:20.894 --> 25:23.313
It'll be epic.

25:23.313 --> 25:25.649
I love you.

25:25.649 --> 25:27.484
I love you, too.

25:27.484 --> 25:29.445
Drop the gun.

25:29.445 --> 25:37.578
♪♪

25:37.578 --> 25:39.496
Show me your hands.
[ Groans ]

25:39.496 --> 25:41.749
♪ There's a promise
in the back room ♪

25:41.749 --> 25:43.792
[ Grunts ] Run!

25:43.792 --> 25:45.461
[ Siren wailing ]

25:45.461 --> 25:47.004
♪ You tell a little lie
and then you ♪

25:47.004 --> 25:49.298
[ Tires screech ]

25:49.298 --> 25:51.759
Suspect Monica Ditmar's
on the loose.

25:51.759 --> 25:53.052
She is armed and dangerous,

25:53.052 --> 25:54.636
wearing a wedding dress
and combat boots.

25:54.636 --> 25:55.929
You go north.

25:58.098 --> 25:59.892
[ Siren wailing ]

26:02.478 --> 26:07.858
♪♪

26:07.858 --> 26:12.780
♪♪

26:12.780 --> 26:14.323
What's the damage?

26:14.323 --> 26:16.033
GSW through-and-through
to the upper back.

26:16.033 --> 26:17.409
They're prepping
the E. R. now.

26:17.409 --> 26:19.036
You should have
turned yourselves in.

26:19.036 --> 26:21.371
[ Chuckles ]
I am unrepentant.

26:21.371 --> 26:23.874
I'll be sure to let
the judge know that.

26:23.874 --> 26:25.584
The question is,
are you going to help me

26:25.584 --> 26:27.336
save Monica's life?

26:27.336 --> 26:29.505
[ Groans ] Let me guess.

26:29.505 --> 26:31.090
You want me to
tell her to give up?

26:31.090 --> 26:32.674
You're damn right I do.

26:32.674 --> 26:34.009
You think what you're
doing is noble?

26:34.009 --> 26:35.803
You think this has
a happy ending?

26:35.803 --> 26:38.388
Grow up.
You shot at cops.

26:38.388 --> 26:41.683
A thousand police officers
are hunting for your wife

26:41.683 --> 26:44.269
as we speak,
and when they catch her

26:44.269 --> 26:46.230
and she tries to shoot her way
to freedom,

26:46.230 --> 26:48.065
she's not gonna survive.

26:48.065 --> 26:51.568
So you're gonna record a message
telling her to surrender.

26:51.568 --> 26:55.239
Or wake up from surgery to
the news that you're a widower.

26:55.239 --> 26:56.573
[ Groans ]

26:56.573 --> 26:58.742
[ Breathing heavily ]

27:00.786 --> 27:02.246
Forget it.

27:02.246 --> 27:04.248
Our entire lives,
we've been ordered around.

27:04.248 --> 27:06.583
I'm not just gonna be another
person telling her what to do.

27:07.334 --> 27:09.002
The O. R.'s ready.

27:09.002 --> 27:10.587
Go ahead.
I'm done with him.

27:11.964 --> 27:13.090
Let's move.

27:13.090 --> 27:17.594
♪♪

27:17.594 --> 27:21.807
I can't tell you how much
your advice means to me.

27:21.807 --> 27:23.058
Thank you.

27:23.058 --> 27:24.768
Of course, Quigley.

27:24.768 --> 27:27.229
And, remember, whenever
you're feeling low,

27:27.229 --> 27:30.524
just tell yourself
those three words.

27:30.524 --> 27:31.984
I'm worth it.

27:33.151 --> 27:35.070
Can I call you "mom"?

27:35.070 --> 27:37.698
I think it's better
if you didn't.

27:37.698 --> 27:39.658
Okay. Thanks again.

27:41.743 --> 27:42.828
[ Jack fusses ]

27:42.828 --> 27:44.246
I'm worth it.

27:44.246 --> 27:45.831
Okay.

27:45.831 --> 27:46.665
Ready to go?

27:46.665 --> 27:48.041
Yes. Thank you.

27:48.041 --> 27:50.711
[ Gasps ] You've had quite
a day, haven't you?

27:50.711 --> 27:53.338
Are you gonna be a lawyer
like your daddy, huh?

27:53.338 --> 27:55.924
Jackson, are you gonna help
the less fortunate?

27:55.924 --> 27:58.760
Mm. Not sure how much
I'm helping these days.

27:58.760 --> 28:00.304
Why? What happened?

28:00.304 --> 28:02.097
I'm just tired of
the uphill battle.

28:02.097 --> 28:03.640
Prosecutors have
all the power.

28:03.640 --> 28:05.559
Well, if you
can't beat them...

28:05.559 --> 28:06.643
Join them?

28:06.643 --> 28:07.895
No. Unh-unh.

28:07.895 --> 28:09.021
Why not?

28:09.021 --> 28:11.440
Are you telling me
that you wouldn't make

28:11.440 --> 28:14.443
a bigger impact
if you had that power?

28:22.117 --> 28:24.703
[ Horses neighs ]

28:31.126 --> 28:33.754
If Daniel told us about
his Mother's Day plans,

28:33.754 --> 28:35.672
how many others
did he tell?

28:35.672 --> 28:38.091
Sgt. Grey: It only takes one
to give him up to his gang.

28:38.091 --> 28:39.760
[ Clears throat ]

28:39.760 --> 28:41.094
Shh, shh, shh, shh.

28:41.094 --> 28:42.638
You're lucky I'm not putting
you in cuffs right now.

28:42.638 --> 28:44.723
I know. I'm sorry.

28:44.723 --> 28:46.308
Go say goodbye
to your mother.

28:46.308 --> 28:47.893
We need to get you back
to the apartment.

28:47.893 --> 28:50.020
Come on. Can't I just spend
the rest of the day with my mom?

28:50.020 --> 28:51.438
No!

28:51.438 --> 28:53.815
You're an informant
in a gang murder trial.

28:53.815 --> 28:55.484
There are people trying
to kill you.

28:55.484 --> 28:58.528
By being here, you're putting
you and your mother in danger.

29:02.074 --> 29:04.117
You're right.
I'll go with you.

29:04.117 --> 29:07.204
But, please, you can't
tell her why you're here.

29:07.204 --> 29:08.538
Excuse me?

29:08.538 --> 29:10.415
My mom doesn't know --
about the gang,

29:10.415 --> 29:12.209
about witness protection,
any of it.

29:12.209 --> 29:13.877
Okay, she's going
to find out.

29:13.877 --> 29:15.629
I know, but I just don't
want to ruin her day.

29:15.629 --> 29:16.546
Please.

29:16.546 --> 29:17.714
Fine, fine.

29:17.714 --> 29:20.258
Hi.
What's going on?

29:20.926 --> 29:24.888
Don't worry, Mom.
This is just about, uh...my car.

29:24.888 --> 29:26.515
It got stolen.

29:26.515 --> 29:28.725
Oh, no, Daniel.
That's terrible.

29:28.725 --> 29:31.019
You just bought it.
I know.

29:31.019 --> 29:33.230
But I didn't want to
worry you today.

29:33.230 --> 29:35.440
You know who did it?

29:35.440 --> 29:37.401
Uh...yes, ma'am.

29:37.401 --> 29:39.528
That's why we need your son
to come with us --

29:39.528 --> 29:41.738
so he can
view the lineup.

29:42.739 --> 29:44.491
I didn't know you
really did that.

29:44.491 --> 29:46.952
Oh, yeah, all the time.
Vital part of police work.

29:48.870 --> 29:54.835
♪♪

29:59.214 --> 30:00.424
Okay, charade's over.

30:00.424 --> 30:01.550
What's going on?
Who are they?

30:02.551 --> 30:03.802
They're here
to kill your son.

30:03.802 --> 30:05.303
What?
We need to find cover.

30:05.303 --> 30:07.222
Take mom,
watch your backstop.

30:07.222 --> 30:08.515
Daniel.
Make sure the horses

30:08.515 --> 30:09.725
don't get hit
in the cross fire.

30:09.725 --> 30:15.105
♪♪

30:15.105 --> 30:20.444
♪♪

30:20.444 --> 30:22.070
[ Horse neighs ]

30:22.070 --> 30:29.953
♪♪

30:29.953 --> 30:37.753
♪♪

30:37.753 --> 30:45.635
♪♪

30:45.635 --> 30:47.012
[ Grunts ]

30:47.012 --> 30:51.016
♪♪

30:51.016 --> 30:52.893
[ Grunting ]

30:52.893 --> 31:00.984
♪♪

31:00.984 --> 31:02.986
[ Horse neighs ]

31:02.986 --> 31:06.990
♪♪

31:06.990 --> 31:08.700
[ Grunting ]

31:08.700 --> 31:12.704
♪♪

31:12.704 --> 31:14.623
[ Grunting ]

31:19.211 --> 31:20.837
Thank you
for the assist.

31:20.837 --> 31:22.380
You're welcome.

31:22.380 --> 31:23.757
On your knees.

31:23.757 --> 31:24.925
Where's Daniel?

31:24.925 --> 31:27.385
He took off.

31:27.385 --> 31:30.555
Sarge, I think we got one more
guy to worry about.

31:30.555 --> 31:32.557
I'll stay with the suspect.
You go find Daniel.

31:32.557 --> 31:34.226
Yes, sir.
I'm going with you.

31:34.226 --> 31:36.478
Uh, Mrs. Tran, thank you.
I-I-I've got this.

31:36.478 --> 31:38.188
He got it. He got it.

31:38.188 --> 31:42.400
♪♪

31:51.493 --> 31:54.454
I know you came in here,
Daniel.

31:58.291 --> 32:00.836
The longer you make me
hunt for you...

32:03.713 --> 32:06.299
...the more times
I'm gonna shoot you.

32:10.220 --> 32:13.056
It's a shame. I thought you were
a stand-up guy.

32:14.391 --> 32:19.604
But you flipped the second
you felt the handcuffs go on.

32:20.981 --> 32:22.399
[ Gunshots ]

32:22.399 --> 32:26.444
♪♪

32:26.444 --> 32:28.071
[ Coughs ]

32:28.071 --> 32:30.740
Give me your hands.
Give me your hands.

32:30.740 --> 32:32.284
[ Handcuffs click ]
Come on.

32:32.284 --> 32:33.326
Get up.

32:33.326 --> 32:35.453
Daniel,
it's safe to come out.

32:39.749 --> 32:41.418
Come on.

32:42.878 --> 32:44.504
[ Elevator bell dings ]

32:47.424 --> 32:56.183
♪♪

32:56.183 --> 33:04.941
♪♪

33:04.941 --> 33:07.027
[ Cellphone rings ]

33:10.739 --> 33:12.115
Hey, hon.

33:12.115 --> 33:14.451
Yeah, I'm on duty
at the hospital.

33:14.451 --> 33:21.666
♪♪

33:21.666 --> 33:28.840
♪♪

33:28.840 --> 33:31.426
Come on, baby.
We gotta go.

33:32.594 --> 33:33.887
Don't move.

33:33.887 --> 33:35.180
W-Where's Jonah?

33:35.180 --> 33:36.681
He's in the ICU.
They think he'll pull through.

33:36.681 --> 33:38.099
Now get your hands up.

33:39.601 --> 33:41.394
I promised I'd put
some bracelets on you,

33:41.394 --> 33:42.771
and I keep my promises.

33:44.648 --> 33:47.692
But, first,
this is mine.

33:50.779 --> 33:52.239
Turn around.

33:52.239 --> 33:55.617
♪♪

33:55.617 --> 33:56.910
Come on.

34:00.247 --> 34:01.998
That was a crazy day.
Mm.

34:01.998 --> 34:03.500
I can't believe Daniel's mom
is going into

34:03.500 --> 34:04.918
witness protection
with him.

34:04.918 --> 34:08.505
She loves him, and he clearly
still needs her.

34:08.505 --> 34:10.799
Thank you for
the one-on-one time today.

34:10.799 --> 34:12.092
I really did
learn a lot.

34:12.092 --> 34:13.134
You're welcome.

34:13.134 --> 34:14.803
And for what it's worth,

34:14.803 --> 34:16.972
I think you're a really good
candidate for FTO.

34:16.972 --> 34:19.641
And I'll tell them that
after you pass your exam.

34:19.641 --> 34:21.184
Thank you.
Yeah.

34:21.184 --> 34:22.644
Ooh!

34:22.644 --> 34:24.187
You still didn't get
anything for Luna.

34:24.187 --> 34:26.606
Actually, I did.
You just didn't notice.

34:26.606 --> 34:28.316
Which means
it's a good thing

34:28.316 --> 34:30.402
you're not trying
to be a detective.

34:31.653 --> 34:33.071
Well,
what'd you get her?

34:33.071 --> 34:38.785
♪♪

34:38.785 --> 34:40.453
It is time to go home.

34:40.453 --> 34:41.913
I have Indian food
on the way.

34:41.913 --> 34:43.164
Where's Jack?

34:43.164 --> 34:44.582
Uh, my mom took him
to Fred Segal.

34:44.582 --> 34:45.750
She's gonna meet us
at home.

34:45.750 --> 34:48.503
That kid has a better
wardrobe than I do.

34:53.258 --> 34:55.510
[ Sighs ]

34:56.636 --> 34:59.180
I'm thinking
of changing jobs.

34:59.180 --> 35:00.265
To what?

35:00.265 --> 35:01.683
[ Chuckles ]

35:01.683 --> 35:04.519
There's an open spot
in the D. A.'s office.

35:05.312 --> 35:07.188
I am literally
without words.

35:07.188 --> 35:09.733
You call them the enemy
like four times a week.

35:09.733 --> 35:11.943
I know.
Because they are.

35:11.943 --> 35:15.155
And I love advocating for people
that are caught in the system,

35:15.155 --> 35:18.033
but I lose more battles
than I win.

35:18.033 --> 35:20.285
Do you think the D. A. can
look past your suspension?

35:20.285 --> 35:22.495
Considering I helped
put away a major drug lord

35:22.495 --> 35:24.623
in the process,
I think so.

35:26.082 --> 35:29.044
If there is even
a 10% chance that I can

35:29.044 --> 35:33.965
change the system from within,
I have to do it.

35:33.965 --> 35:35.467
Don't I?

35:35.467 --> 35:37.218
I can't answer that
for you.

35:38.386 --> 35:41.014
But we can talk about it
over Indian food.

35:41.014 --> 35:42.682
Deal.

35:42.682 --> 35:44.559
Thank you.

35:46.978 --> 35:49.022
I love you.
I love you, too.

35:49.022 --> 35:51.191
Hey, I'm about to head out.
You good?

35:51.191 --> 35:52.859
Uh, yeah.
I'm just finishing up.

35:52.859 --> 35:53.943
I'm -- I'm right
behind you.

35:53.943 --> 35:55.654
Okay.
See you tomorrow.

35:55.654 --> 36:01.451
♪♪

36:01.451 --> 36:04.412
♪ I believe in silence ♪

36:05.205 --> 36:08.083
♪ There's something
in the quiet ♪

36:09.084 --> 36:10.877
♪ But you were always talking ♪

36:10.877 --> 36:11.920
Lila: Mommy!

36:13.338 --> 36:16.633
Hi, baby girl.
What are you doing here?

36:16.633 --> 36:17.967
Nana brought me.

36:17.967 --> 36:20.178
Maris, w-w-what's going on?
Is Donovan okay?

36:20.178 --> 36:21.513
Oh, he's fine.

36:21.513 --> 36:23.598
Except for this really weird
rash that just showed up.

36:23.598 --> 36:27.060
That and the fact that I clearly
didn't raise him right.

36:27.060 --> 36:30.105
Keeping a mother from
her child on Mother's Day?

36:30.105 --> 36:32.565
I mean, what is
wrong with him?

36:32.565 --> 36:34.317
Thank you.
[ Chuckles ]

36:34.317 --> 36:36.736
You don't know how much
that means to me.

36:36.736 --> 36:38.363
Yeah, I do.

36:38.363 --> 36:41.991
Listen, I-I know
I haven't done a good job

36:41.991 --> 36:43.743
of keeping in touch.

36:43.743 --> 36:45.578
No, t-that is not
a problem.

36:45.578 --> 36:48.373
I know this whole thing
is complicated.

36:48.373 --> 36:53.503
Yeah, maybe so,
but it doesn't matter

36:53.503 --> 36:56.214
what happened between
you and Donovan.

36:56.214 --> 37:03.179
You will always be
the daughter I never had.

37:03.179 --> 37:06.141
♪ So I'm looking ahead ♪
Thank you.

37:07.851 --> 37:11.396
♪ I could see you moving ♪

37:11.396 --> 37:14.357
♪ To a building on Logan ♪

37:15.024 --> 37:16.943
Hi.
Hi!

37:17.777 --> 37:18.903
Good day?

37:18.903 --> 37:20.363
Yeah, it was okay.

37:20.363 --> 37:22.615
Lucy was particularly
annoying, but --

37:22.615 --> 37:24.576
I don't believe
that for a second.

37:25.493 --> 37:29.205
Hey, I know we said Hyatt,
but I just found

37:29.205 --> 37:32.542
this super-cute Sharebnb
in Ko Olina.

37:32.542 --> 37:34.002
Cozier, right?

37:34.002 --> 37:35.462
Just the two of us?

37:35.462 --> 37:36.838
That's romantic.

37:36.838 --> 37:39.007
♪ And hold your head ♪

37:39.007 --> 37:42.010
Is -- Is that, uh --
Is that a new nail color?

37:42.969 --> 37:44.929
Yeah.
I just had them done.

37:44.929 --> 37:46.973
Oh.

37:46.973 --> 37:49.225
They're --
They're pretty.

37:49.225 --> 37:50.852
Yeah?

37:50.852 --> 37:53.396
Uh, I'm sorry.

37:53.396 --> 37:55.148
Ashley, look.
I-I need to --

37:55.148 --> 37:58.067
I need to clear the air
about something here.

37:58.067 --> 38:00.361
The reason Lucy was
so annoying today

38:00.361 --> 38:02.572
is that she is convinced
that you think

38:02.572 --> 38:04.949
I'm taking you
to Hawaii to propose.

38:04.949 --> 38:07.702
But, I mean, you don't --
you don't think that, right?

38:07.702 --> 38:09.078
'C-Cause I'm not.

38:09.078 --> 38:12.123
I mean, I-I think we are
magic together, but I --

38:12.123 --> 38:14.000
Shh!

38:15.335 --> 38:17.045
It's okay.

38:17.045 --> 38:20.548
♪ You turn me red ♪

38:20.548 --> 38:24.552
[ Laughs ] I am not
expecting a proposal.

38:24.552 --> 38:25.470
Okay.

38:25.470 --> 38:28.097
I would say "no"
if you asked.

38:28.097 --> 38:33.186
Uh, don't get me wrong.
I think we're magic, too.

38:33.186 --> 38:37.148
But I just have
no interest in ever

38:37.148 --> 38:39.067
being married
or having kids.

38:39.067 --> 38:42.195
I'm just not wired
that way.

38:43.404 --> 38:45.240
Oh.

38:45.240 --> 38:46.366
Okay.

38:46.366 --> 38:48.701
Uh, great.

38:48.701 --> 38:50.787
It's a vacation.
[ Laughs ]

38:50.787 --> 38:52.121
Look, we're gonna have
a great time.

38:52.121 --> 38:53.289
Yes, we will.

38:53.289 --> 38:54.833
[ Laughs ]

38:57.919 --> 38:59.087
Will you do me a favor?

39:08.263 --> 39:10.598
Hey.
Oh, hi.

39:10.598 --> 39:12.767
So, it's a good thing you
didn't come to meet my mom,

39:12.767 --> 39:14.602
because she drove me
absolutely crazy.

39:14.602 --> 39:15.603
[ Chuckles ]

39:15.603 --> 39:16.771
What's wrong?

39:16.771 --> 39:18.857
Nothing. I --
[ Cellphone chimes ]

39:18.857 --> 39:20.859
♪♪

39:20.859 --> 39:22.193
[ Horn honks ]

39:24.988 --> 39:26.197
Could you just
wait here?

39:26.197 --> 39:27.782
I need to go find Lopez
and figure out

39:27.782 --> 39:29.117
how to put a curse
on someone.

39:29.117 --> 39:30.785
[ Laughs ] Yeah, right.

39:31.703 --> 39:32.954
Oh, you're serious.

39:33.830 --> 39:35.290
Luna:
Where are you taking me?

39:35.290 --> 39:36.624
Sgt. Grey:
Still a surprise.

39:36.624 --> 39:38.251
Alright.
My lady.

39:38.251 --> 39:39.419
I didn't cheat.
I'm not peeking.

39:39.419 --> 39:40.962
Yeah, okay. Alright.
I'm here. I'm ready.

39:40.962 --> 39:41.963
I believe you.

39:41.963 --> 39:43.464
Oh, honey.

39:43.464 --> 39:45.758
[ Laughs ]

39:45.758 --> 39:48.428
I know it's been hard
not having Dominique here.

39:48.428 --> 39:50.513
First Mother's Day
without her.

39:50.513 --> 39:54.517
So I wanted to do something
special for you.

39:54.517 --> 39:56.227
Oh, really?
'Cause I thought those flowers

39:56.227 --> 39:59.272
you sent earlier
was just gonna be it.

39:59.272 --> 40:01.316
That was all
an elaborate ruse, my dear.

40:01.316 --> 40:02.609
[ Laughs ] Okay.

40:02.609 --> 40:05.278
Are you ready?

40:05.278 --> 40:06.571
[ Laughs ] Ready.
You ready?

40:06.571 --> 40:07.697
I'm ready,
I'm ready, yes.

40:07.697 --> 40:08.740
You ready?
Yes.

40:08.740 --> 40:09.991
[ Laughs ]
Alright, here we go.

40:09.991 --> 40:11.701
And voilà.

40:11.701 --> 40:12.994
[ Gasps ]

40:12.994 --> 40:14.829
[ Horse whinnies ]
You bought me a horse.

40:14.829 --> 40:16.873
No.
Riding lessons.

40:16.873 --> 40:18.416
[ Both laugh ]

40:18.416 --> 40:19.542
Oh!

40:19.542 --> 40:23.212
Plus, a romantic
Mother's Day night ride

40:23.212 --> 40:24.923
around the property
with me.

40:24.923 --> 40:26.674
Sound good?
Yes.

40:26.674 --> 40:28.718
I love it.
Oh, thank you.

40:28.718 --> 40:30.178
Alright, go.

40:30.178 --> 40:32.680
Go play. Go.
[ Laughs ]

40:32.680 --> 40:34.349
Hi.

40:34.349 --> 40:35.683
I'm gonna get you to
buy her for me.

40:35.683 --> 40:36.559
[ Both laugh ]

40:36.559 --> 40:38.353
[ Horse whinnies ]

40:38.353 --> 40:45.568
♪♪

40:45.568 --> 40:47.070
[ Knock on door ]

40:57.121 --> 40:58.831
Hey!
What a surprise.

40:58.831 --> 41:01.084
Come in.
Let me get you a drink.

41:01.876 --> 41:04.879
So...how was
horseback riding?

41:04.879 --> 41:06.631
Beautiful.

41:06.631 --> 41:10.093
Wade said that you
helped him find it.

41:10.093 --> 41:11.719
Nolan:
Something like that.

41:11.719 --> 41:13.054
But you guys didn't
come all this way

41:13.054 --> 41:15.056
just to thank me
for that.

41:16.557 --> 41:18.559
No.

41:18.559 --> 41:21.187
I just received
a formal request

41:21.187 --> 41:23.523
to temporarily assign you
to another station.

41:23.523 --> 41:25.525
My first day
in the hole.

41:25.525 --> 41:26.651
Cool.

41:28.444 --> 41:29.821
Not cool?

41:29.821 --> 41:32.699
No. This request
is for the whole week.

41:32.699 --> 41:34.409
That means I'll miss
my T. O. exam.

41:34.409 --> 41:35.785
Exactly.

41:35.785 --> 41:38.579
And before you start
plotting how to sneak back

41:38.579 --> 41:40.957
and take it on your lunch hour,
the station you're going to

41:40.957 --> 41:42.959
is four hours away,
on the border.

41:42.959 --> 41:45.044
This is my punishment

41:45.044 --> 41:46.587
for pissing off
the Union President.

41:46.587 --> 41:48.548
He knows I want
to be a T. O.

41:48.548 --> 41:49.966
Yeah.

41:49.966 --> 41:52.802
Isn't there anything
you can do?

41:52.802 --> 41:55.513
I would if I could,
but my hands are tied.

41:55.513 --> 41:59.100
If you try to
reject the assignment,

41:59.100 --> 42:02.645
they will consider it
disobeying a direct order.

42:02.645 --> 42:05.481
So even if you pass the test,
they wouldn't make you a T. O.

42:05.481 --> 42:07.650
if you're facing
disciplinary action.

42:09.318 --> 42:12.196
Well, then you are just gonna
have to take the next test.

42:12.196 --> 42:13.531
When is it?

42:13.531 --> 42:15.825
In two years.

42:15.825 --> 42:20.705
♪♪

42:28.755 --> 42:37.096
♪♪

42:37.096 --> 42:45.480
♪♪

42:45.480 --> 42:53.738
♪♪
